raw_data.title: Interview Architect ®Express Interviewer's Kit - Competency Level 2nd Edition
raw_data.description: Interview Architect® Express Interviewer’s Kit offers quality of hire and speed of process with interviewing tools that are flexible and easy to use. With the Competency Level version, interviewers can assess candidates on 67 Competencies, 19 Career Stallers and Stoppers and 7 Global Focus Areas. Interview Architect® Express is for: Hiring managers looking to conduct interviews in a structured, standardized format; HR professionals who want a straightforward means to evaluate candidates; Managers unfamiliar with the structured interview process. In addition to the Competency Set, Interview Architect® Express Interviewer’s Kit is also available in Complete Set version. All versions feature: A user-friendly layout with easy-to-read typefaces and graphics; Specially designed note pad that facilitates quick, accurate note taking; Unique Post-It™ pen to flag key questions; Usage Guide that addresses how to work with each of the interviewing areas.

raw_data.title: Interview Architect ®Express Refill Notepads (Pack of 5)

Interview Architect® Express is for: Hiring managers looking to conduct interviews in a structured, standardized format; HR professionals who want a straightforward means to evaluate candidates; Managers unfamiliar with the structured interview process. The Interview Architect® Express Interviewer’s Kit is available in a Competency Level version, a Factor and Cluster Level version and a Complete Set that includes the Competency Level and Factor and Cluster Level versions. All three versions feature: A user-friendly layout with easy-to-read typefaces and graphics; Specially designed note pad that facilitates quick, accurate note taking; Unique Post-It™ pen to flag key questions; Usage Guide that addresses how to work with each of the interviewing areas.

labor_categories.labor_category: Interview Architect ® Learning and Application Guide

raw_data.title: Interview Architect ® Learning and Application Guide
raw_data.description: Interview Architect® Learning and Application Guide is part of a comprehensive Interview Architect® Trainer’s Tool Set created to streamline and enhance efforts to implement Interview Architect® in an organization. The Interview Architect® Learning and Application Guide is for: Hiring managers who are using Interview Architect® Express on a day-to-day basis; Training professionals to use in guiding managers through the structured interview process. Interview Architect® Learning and Application Guide includes: Step-by-step guidance on planning, conducting and evaluating an Interview Architect® Express interview; Several interactive exercises to promote interviewing skill development; A tear-out Job Aid that summarizes key points for quick reference. Interview Architect® Learning and Application Guide requires certification to purchase.

raw_data.title: Consultant
raw_data.description: Demonstrated ability to ensure quality delivery of products to consultants and clients in the Human Resources, Talent Development, and/or Compensation & Benefits areas of delivery -including obtaining and adhering to changing project requirements. Proven ability to produce accurate, edited work and communicate project parameters to others on project team.

raw_data.title: Junior Consultant
raw_data.description: Demonstrated ability to perform technical and administrative assistance to support Human Resources, Leadership and Talent Development, and/or Compensation & Benefits project teams; and work to coordinate and meet deliverable deadlines. Also conduct analysis and research in support of projects.

raw_data.title: Mid Consultant
raw_data.description: Demonstrated ability to ensure quality delivery of Human Resources, Leadership and Talent Development, and Compensation & Benefits program services to consultants and clients – including obtaining and adhering to changing project requirements; produce accurate, edited work.

raw_data.title: Principal
raw_data.description: Demonstrated ability to provide guidance and direction for multiple projects and in designing, implementing and managing Human Resources, Talent Development, and/or Compensation & Benefits Projects. Ability to manage and coordinate consulting projects in terms of people, budget and work plans to ensure a cohesive effort and satisfied clients. Ability to leverage one’s own expertise and in-depth knowledge of practice area to best advantage in design and analysis of project work.

raw_data.title: Program Director
raw_data.description: Provide consulting to directors and senior managers on implementation of agency-wide Human Resources and Leadership Development and/or Compensation & Benefits programs. Develop, lead, and conduct quality workshops seminars, training sessions, and facilitation. Customize material for an organization and its specific needs. Lead and conduct benchmarking and surveys for an organization. Facilitate human resources improvement efforts requiring a mastery of technical subject matter and experience in specific programs or processes. Manage a team of consultants and analysts supporting an agency’s human resources and leadership development programs. Generate papers and documents.

raw_data.title: Program Manager
raw_data.description: Demonstrated ability for managing and overseeing work performance on one or more projects in the Human Resources, Talent Development and/or Compensation & Benefits areas of delivery. Holds responsibility for planning, managing and overseeing work efforts of project team personnel, determining and monitoring project personnel, determining and monitoring project schedules and budgets, and/or ensuring compliance with all contract and project requirements and quality standards. Serves as the primary interface with the customer. Demonstrates skills in the scope of work encompassed by the project, provides technical guidance to the project team in performance of the work, and provides quality review of all work products.

raw_data.title: Senior Consultant
raw_data.description: Demonstrated ability to provide analytical, conceptual and process support services to clients and to the consultants who manage the clients in the Human Resources, Talent Development, and/or Compensation & Benefits areas of delivery. Ability to implement and deliver technical and process consulting through management of standard consulting projects.

raw_data.title: Senior Manager
raw_data.description: Demonstrated ability in managing, implementing and delivering Human Resources, Talent Development, and/or Compensation & Benefits Projects. Ability to provide technical and consulting expertise on a wide variety of consulting assignments. Manage moderately complex project work and assist with large projects. Provide research and analysis relating to area of specialty. Establish credibility with the members of the client’s management staff.

labor_categories.labor_category: Learning From Experience ™ (LFE) Interview Guide (pack of 10)

raw_data.title: Learning From Experience ™ (LFE) Interview Guide (pack of 10)
raw_data.description: Learning From Experience™ (LFE) Interview Guide is a human resources tool designed to assist employers with the interviewing process. The Guide helps organizations build future bench strength through interviewing and selecting the most learning agile internal and external candidates. Learning From Experience™ (LFE) Interviewing is for: Hiring managers looking to conduct deep learning agility interviews in a structured, standardized format; HR professionals who want a straightforward means to evaluate a candidate’s ability to learn from experience; Succession planning teams interested in building future leaders. Learning From Experience™ (LFE) Interviewing uses four types of learning agility—mental, people, change, and results agility, and a three step process to aid in learning from experience interviewing: Pre-interview—Identify the related learning agility factors—mental, people, change, and results agility; During the interview—Use the learning agility factors to rate the candidate; After the interview—Consolidate learning agility findings on the Learning From Experience Conclusions pages. Learning From Experience™ (LFE) Interview Guides require certification to purchase.

raw_data.title: viaEDGE 1-10 Employees
raw_data.description: viaEDGE™ self-assessment measures an learning agility, individual’s ability and willingness to learn from experience—and perform successfully in new situations. Distinct from intelligence — learning agility is the single, best predictor of high-potential. viaEDGE™ easily and efficiently gauges the potential of large numbers of individuals, with the ease of an online self-administered assessment. viaEDGE™ helps organizations: Assess internal talent for placement and development of high potentials; Aid in external candidate hiring; Identify managers most likely to succeed in international assignments. viaEDGE™ measures the five dimensions of learning agility — mental, people, change, results,and  self-awareness. The viaEDGE™ assessment takes about 30 minutes. Summary results are delivered immediately, with in depth results and interpretation delivered though Korn/Ferry certified coaches.
